				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ r=\rho +\eta\ g $$\end{document}where r = social time discount rate (%); ρ = rate of pure time preference (%); η = slope of the marginal utility function for consumption (−); and g = average growth rate of per capita consumption (%).

A formula for the time discounting of investments is the consumption based capital asset pricing model (CCAPM), after Lucas (1978):9R=Rf+βπ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
