				\begin{document}$$ R={R}_{\mathrm{f}}+\beta\ \pi $$\end{document}where R = investment-specific expected return adjusted for risk (%); Rf = risk­free rate in financial markets (%); β = elasticity of climate damages with respect to changes in aggregate consumption (−); and π = systematic or market risk premium (%).

