A point of technical clarification is that currency trading does not register in GWP and the issuance of 4C rewards does not register in GWP4C. If the 4C parallel currency is used to buy goods and services, then that trade with 4C will register in GWP4C, but if 4C is not used to buy goods and services and is only used to trade currencies, then GWP4C reduces to zero. The default policy is that 4C is only used to trade currencies, and so GWP4C is dropped, and Eq. (11) is rearranged to yield the following expression for ΔQzero, which is the quantity of mitigation rewarded by 4C that achieves net zero CO2 emissions:12ΔQzerot≅ctλωt∑i=1tGWPi\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
